==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Republicanism
<hw>Re*pub"lic*an*ism</hw> <pr>(-?z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧publicanisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A republican
form or system of government; the principles or theory of republican
government.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Attachment to, or political sympathy for, a
republican form of government.</def> <rj><au>Burke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The principles and policy of the Republican party,
so called</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Republicanize</ent>⟦br⟧
